            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I've added info about how to set up the app context.\r\n\r\n> This seems like the exact same as the celery pattern. Why do we need another doc?\r\n\r\nThey are indeed very close. I figured this'd be useful to someone trying to decide what to use, but if it isn't that's OK too. :)\r\n\r\n> There's also the issue of maintenance. Keeping this up to date will fall on the Flask community. Maybe it's better to make a mention of Dramatiq and link to the project documentation specific to Flask?\r\n\r\n@wgwz The APIs documented here are unlikely to change, but you make a valid point. I'd be happy to maintain it though I realise that doesn't mean much from a first-time contributor. What would be a good place to put that mention if we go that route?\r\n\r\nI also forgot to leave a disclaimer in my OP, sorry about that! I am the creator of Dramatiq.\r\n"
        },
