            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The current [pattern](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/0.12/patterns/celery/) could be made somewhat tool agnostic. Then it could mention \"here are different ways to handle background tasks\". It could even start from threading like is done [here](https://blog.miguelgrinberg.com/post/the-flask-mega-tutorial-part-xi-email-support) for emails, and extending into more advanced cases. I think the Celery snippet is important to keep, because it is widely used and the Celery docs don't have anything specific to Flask. So in this case you could add a link potentially as \"Here are more tools for task handling\". \r\n\r\nBut I'm not regular contributor, so we will have to see what others think. :) "
        },
